    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CPB hemolysis worst-case identification, Class II, MRL 2) is accepted based on the following structured evidence: (1) All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required Gradation levels — discretization error achieves Gradation 3 against a Gradation 2 requirement, providing additional confidence margin. (2) The 6 scoped-out factors are appropriately excluded per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 for MRL 2, with documented rationale for each. (3) Three independent validation results (pressure head, hemolysis index, velocity field) all meet pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria with uncertainty quantification. (4) The validation activities use the same FDA generic pump geometry and representative operating conditions, establishing high relevance to the COU. (5) The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion is directly linked to the clinical endpoint and regulatory guidance. (6) No credibility gaps or shortfalls are identified. The model is assessed as fit for the stated purpose of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
